txt.en: Ekhamât Triumphant
Cheer on faltering Subuzûri ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
'Thank you. I should be able to manage from here.'
Tend to wounded Subuzûri ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
'What a glorious battle, isn't it!? Back to the fray!'
'That's a lot of blood. Well, that should hold for now!'
'I feel better already. They shall know our fury!'

'He played me for a fool. Damn my temper. It feels sometimes like a flame that consumes the rest of me whole. We need to end the threat here, and then we need to warn the others as quickly as possible. I thought there more forces in reserve, but clearly he only left a small portion of his army.\n\n'Please, help finish the fighting here, and then I have an even more important task for you.'
'Thank you for your haste in seeking me out. I received a disturbing report from one of my scouts that I would discuss with you.'
'This is not the real battle. I need to warn the leaders of Khûd Zagin and Ambarûl. They are in terrible danger.'
